   Trilobites, a dominant Cambrian animal, lso occur in the Burgess Shale in abundance. Trilobites
   are an extinct group of arthropods that were most dominant in the Cambrain before finally
   becoming extinct at the close of the Paleozoic. Like Marella and other arthropods, trilobites
   have a hard exoskeleton (that enhanced the chances of fossilization) and numerous jointed
   appendages. In the trilobite shown, details of the appendages are not clear.

