   This rare specimen (L) of a Silurian crinoid, Icthyocrinus sp., from the Rochester Shale of New
   York illustrates the three regions of the body that can be often found as isolated fossils. The
   specimen of Caryocrinites ornatus (R) shows details of the stalk and head region. Images from
